      "date": "2013-09-04 16:45:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(5 inline comments)\n\nThank you, Andreas.\n\n``Feel free to be generous with tab conversion, since we are trying to move everything over to tabs for the next release.''\n\nI know you are trying to do that.  How is this for a suggestion:  in one patch, tabify every line that is either purely commentary or hasn't been touched since the 1.8 series.  That way, \"git blame\" still works on stuff changed reasonably recently and most of the \"this is a small section, please tabify it\" comments will be reduced substantially.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
